1.	The Defendant shall have no contact with persons under the age of 14 , except may have in person contact with persons under age 14 when such contact is directly supervised by a sober person over age 18. No contact includes no contact through third persons, and no contact through any other means of communication including no telephone, text messaging or other forms of electronic communication.
2.	No contact with L. Doe, L. Doe's residence, or any immediate family members of L. Doe. No contact includes:  a.) No contact in person:  b.) Doe or his immediate family members.
